  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "\r\n#### System information\r\nGeth version: 1.8.21-stable\r\nOS & Version: Linux, Debian GNU/Linux 9\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\nAfter running (synchronized) for a long period of time and being abruptly terminated we expect upon restart to quickly re-synchronize.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\nUpon restart the node appears to restart synchronization from a very early point in time, when it had previously reached synchronization.\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\n1. Run the node synchronized for a period of time.\r\n2. Abruptly kill the node (kill -9 or system crash).\r\n3. Restart the node, observe where it resynchronizes from.\r\n\r\n",
