    "body": "It does flush the state trie periodically, IIRC it's after an hours worth of block processing time. If we estimate block processing time to `200ms`, that means the default settings will flush every 18K blocks or so. That can be modified via the `TrieTimeLimit`, which I could've sworn was configurable via either command line options or toml. \r\n\r\n@karalabe did we not make that configurable? ",
