    "body": "I'm closing this; works as expected. \r\nIt deliberately does not flush more than the once every couple of hours, to increase in-memory pruning efficiency, reduce disk usage size and disk IO.\r\n\r\n\r\nA graceful shutdown correctly flushes to disk, whereas 'abruptly' killing the node causes memory content to disappear. I don't see how geth could behave differently. ",
